He allegedly shot the learner at Bishops School of Skills on Monday, wounding him in the leg. CAPE TOWN - Police have confirmed the arrest of a 15-year old boy who allegedly shot and wounded a learner at a Bishop Lavis school. He allegedly shot the learner at Bishops School of Skills on Monday, wounding him in the leg. The Western Cape Education Department has implemented extra security at the school for the rest of the week due to the shooting. The police s Noloyiso Rwexana said: He will appear in the Bishop Lavis Magistrates Court today, facing an attempted murder charge after a shooting incident which occurred on Monday. 